1. **initial_sync** — Bulk-download blocks from peers via `BeaconBlocksByRange` RPC. The node
   selects peers by advertised head_slot, pipelines range requests, validates batches (BLS,
   state transition, consensus), applies them to advance fork-choice, and loops until the local
   head reaches the network target slot. Then switches to regular_sync.
{% if language == "Go" %}   Entry points: `beacon-chain/sync/initial-sync/`, `blocksFetcher`, FSM in `*Service`{% endif %}
{% if language == "Rust" and client_name == "lighthouse" %}   Entry points: `beacon_node/network/src/sync/range_sync/`, `RangeSync`, `SyncingChain`{% endif %}
{% if language == "Rust" and client_name == "grandine" %}   Entry points: `fork_choice_control/`, sync manager{% endif %}
{% if language == "Java" %}   Entry points: `beacon/sync/`, `ForwardSync`, `SyncManager`, `PeerSync`{% endif %}
{% if language == "TypeScript" %}   Entry points: `packages/beacon-node/src/sync/range/`, `RangeSync`, `SyncChain`{% endif %}

2. **regular_sync** — Maintains chain head via GossipSub. Subscribes to `beacon_block`,
   `beacon_attestation`, `beacon_aggregate_and_proof`, etc. Validates received blocks (slot,
   proposer, BLS, state transition), imports them, updates fork-choice. Handles missing parents
   via `BeaconBlocksByRoot`. Falls back to range sync if too far behind.
{% if language == "Go" %}   Entry points: `beacon-chain/sync/`, `receiveBlock`, `receiveAttestation`{% endif %}
{% if language == "Rust" and client_name == "lighthouse" %}   Entry points: `beacon_node/network/src/sync/`, `NetworkBeaconProcessor`{% endif %}
